```
/* The only geometory you need to know to solve this problem is that a 'non-zero 
area triangle' is any triangle where c < a + b.  If you take any one side of a 
triangle (C) and it's less than the sum of the other two, (A + B) and then do the same
for all sides, and if they're all true, than it is a valid (non zero area) triangle.  
However, if you start with the highest Int in a set of 3 sides you don't need to 
test all 3 sides. If the highest Int of the 3 sides is less than the sum of the other 
2 than we can conclude that the triangle is non-zero area triangle.
*/

class Solution {

    func largestPerimeter(_ nums: [Int]) -> Int {

        // Sort array of ints in descending order
        let x = nums.sorted(by: >)

        /* Loop through the sorted array in chunks of 3 Ints checking if the 
		first (highest) Int is less than the sum of the second and third,  until 
		you reach the end. At each iteration the largest int will always be at 
		the front therefore if it is a non-zero triangle all other sides will also 
		result in a non-zero solution in which case you can just reutrn the 
		sum of all sides for the highest perimeter triangle.
		*/
        for (i, _) in x.enumerated() where i <= x.count - 3 {
            if x[i] < x[i + 1] + x[i + 2] {
                return x[i] + x[i + 1] + x[i + 2]
            }
        }
        // If we exit the loop without finding any non-zero solutions we return 0
        return 0
    }

}
```

